						               													<description>From the box description...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;I woke last night shaking from a frightful dream. We have come to the edge of the ocean and there is no advancing or retreating.  My own sons may sink in the torrent.  I wish I pray that there be some decent honorable way to put an end to this conflict.  Tone once again reconciled  old friends.  Out cause is righteous and I have no doubt of final success.  But I see out generation and perhaps our hole loaned drowned in blood&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sarah Scott was an English novelist, translator, social reformer, and member of the Bluestockings.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Warriors of the America is a fast playing game on the American War of Independence.  Inspired by the very well received game, Warriors of God, this game features the leaders, soldiers, and events that were pivotal in this history changing war.  Players control leaders, soldiers, and fleets on a map that features both the wilds of North America and the more civilized colonized areas.  Major events will shape each season.  The American player must contend with raising money and a less-trained but highly motivated army while preventing the greatest army in the world, the British Army, from snuffing out the fire of the greatest enlightenment of human rights yet seen on earth.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
